
According to a new report from Intel Market Research, the global Nail Bag Market was valued at USD 794 million in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 1,084 million by 2034, exhibiting a robust CAGR of 4.7% during the forecast period (2025–2034). This growth is driven by rising construction activities, increased DIY home‑improvement projects, and growing awareness of ergonomic tool storage solutions.
A nail bag, also known as a waist bag, is a tool designed to be worn around the waist and holds tools such as screwdrivers and nippers, as well as hardware such as nails and screws. They are used in a wide range of situations, from the workplace to the home. Various types are available, varying in the number of bags, depth of the bags, and materials. Many for home use are simple and easy to handle; some are specialized in design. Selecting the right nail bag for the tools you want to store will greatly increase work efficiency.
